For 2014 pattern :
15 online , 15 theory  & total 40 compulsory
( 2 marks grace for head and 3 marks grace for total )

For 2015 pattern:

Theory marks 20 and total 40 required. No condition for online. 2 grace marks for theory ( 18 marks means pass ) and  3 geace marks on total.

If only 1 Subject back then 10% grace marks will be given

22/12/20, 9:34 pm - +91 70152 41319: Savitribai Phule Pune University (formerly Pune University) Circular Kr. 126/2020 Subject: - Regarding the demonstration / oral / seminar / project / session examination to be organized for the first session (October / November 2020) of the academic year 2020-21 .. Due to the outbreak of Kovid-19 Corona outbreak, educational activities in all the colleges affiliated to the university could be started directly. No. As a result, college students have not been able to demonstrate using laboratories and other technical equipment. In such a situation, these demonstrations will be held only after the regular commencement of colleges. All these issues were discussed in the meeting of various authority board of Savitribai Phule Pune University. In this regard, as per the decision taken by the University Authority, it is informed that all the (written / oral) examinations of the first and second level of the College 2020-21, such as the demonstration / oral / seminar / project / session of the academic year session of the regular students of all the affiliated colleges. Session wise examinations should be conducted separately for the second session (March / April 2021) of the academic year 202021. Also, while filling the examination application form of these regular students, without any change in the process of filling the Online Exam Form, along with the written examinations, the information of the examinations mentioned in the Demonstration / Oral / Seminar / Project / Session and other courses should be filled in the prevailing manner However, in order to avoid technical difficulties, the results of the first semester university examinations of these regular students will be announced only online and the original marks of the first and second semesters will be sent to the college separately along with the marks of the second semester. It is further informed that the practical / oral / seminar / project / session examination of the backlog students will be conducted as usual and the results of their first session will be announced after the written examination. Ma. Principals / Directors, all affiliated colleges / accredited institutions are requested to inform the students, teachers, non-teaching staff and all concerned about the content of this circular and take further necessary action as per this circular. (Mahesh Kakade) Reference: Examination-Coordination / 443 Director Date: 22/12/2020 Examination and Evaluation Board for copy information and appropriate action: - Hon. Principal / Director, all affiliated colleges and accredited institutions.

07/01/21, 9:11 am - +91 70152 41319: *These are the tentative decisions, subject to change as per the University guidelines*

The Director had a talk with the Vice-Chancellor of the university to get better insights on how the college reopening will take place as per the university guidelines.

1) It is compulsory for Electronics and Mechanical students to reach the campus in the specified time period for the Practicals. They MUST produce a NEGATIVE RT-PCR Covid report not older than 72 hours of the commencement of their journey.
However, the following students can be allowed to join late -
a)Whose parent(s)/guardian(s) refuse to give their consent to send their ward to campus after informing the administration.
b)Who have applied for CDS/AFCAT exams and have their center in their hometowns or away from Pune.
c) The students who are currently suffering from some serious health issue or/and are currently Covid positive.
For the above-mentioned students, the Director has proposed a second slot for the Practical classes. It is still not confirmed if this proposal will be accepted.

2) IT and Computer department students have not been called yet and unless SPPU releases the examination schedule, they are likely to remain at their homes. The expected date for the same is January end or February start. 
It is likely that if the examination will be held in online mode, these students would continue to remain at their homes. They are expected to be called if offline conduction of examination is proposed by the University.

3) If any parent/guardian has confusion regarding anything else, they can contact the administration.

4) For accommodation in hostels, it is decided that 2 students would be accommodated in a triplet, and one in a double and singlet. Students will be kept in their old rooms only, some might need to relocate as per the social distancing norms.

Further detailed notices are expected from the administration in a couple of days to clear all possible doubts.

_*TTA's Sunday 17th  January 2021 @ 10 AM (38th) Lecture meeting*_
 
This 38th webinar is organized by Technology Transfer Association (TTA) 

*Sub :Lithium  ion battery Pack Assembly & Manufacturing*

*Speaker* : _*Dr Yashodhan Pramod Gokhale*_
Vice President, Business Development*

Octillion Power Systems India Pvt. Ltd. Plot no. 302,Sector 10, Bhosari MIDC, Pune-411026, India

(cell) +91 9686031328 

www.octillion.us

10:00 AM  |  India Time (Mumbai, GMT+05:30)  |  1 hr

 
17th  January 2021 

*Synopsis*:  
 
Manufacturing of Li-Ion Battery pack is technology by itself. The cell balancing (active as well as passive) is critical success factor. It is a  technology by itself.

Dr Yashodhan Gokhale  will take us  virtually through  manufacturing process and explain   state of the art battery assembly Technology.

28/01/21, 1:49 pm - +91 89996 19378: Greetings,

The word out there is that Felicity's grandeur will continue and you can be a part of it. FELICITY is the annual techno-cultural fest of IIIT Hyderabad. It has always been electrifying and memorable with participation from all over India. Felicity is back for 2021, kicking into the online mode with more enthusiasm and energy. A vivid range of events has been planned which ensures that everyone finds events matching their interests.

Join and become a Campus Ambassador, to be a part of a unique experience while Felicity lives up to its name, right from the comfort of your home. 

Also, enjoy the perks of being a campus ambassador:
1. *Certificate from Felicity, IIIT H*
2. *Free passes to all workshops*
3. *MERCH from Felicity, IIIT H* would be given to a particular college and campus ambassador based on participation

*FAQs*
1) What would my role be as a campus ambassador?
- To promote Felicity events in your respective colleges.

2) Is there any criteria to apply for the CAP (Campus Ambassador Program)?
- You need to be a student pursuing a degree in a college.

3) What additional benefits do I get as a campus ambassador?
- As a CA, you will get additional perks from Felicity depending on your performance.

4) Past Felicity videos:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ypl51RXFHTM
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j7MWQ2RRilI

A limited number of people can apply for CAP from each college and their selection would be decided on *FCFS*, so fill the form ASAP:

03/02/21, 8:15 pm - Vash Dalal: Regarding starting regular classes in all non-agricultural universities, reputed universities, self-financed universities and their affiliated colleges in the state.  Government of Maharashtra Department of Higher and Technical Education Government Circular No.: Sankir 2021 / Q.No.6 / Vishi-3, Mantralaya, Mumbai 400 032, Dated: 03 February, 2021.  References: - (1) University Grants Commission's guidelines dated November 5, 2020.  (2) Minutes of the meeting held on 1st February, 2021.  1.  Introduction: The daily work of educational institutions has been disrupted since March 2020 due to the announcement of lockdown across the country due to the outbreak of the virus Covid-19.  However, the number of Covid-19 infected patients in the state has come down drastically and at present the outbreak seems to be under control.  Therefore, it will be in the interest of the students to start regular classes offline in all the universities and affiliated colleges in the state by taking general preventive measures.  Accordingly, the matter of starting regular classes in all the universities and affiliated colleges in the state was under consideration by the government.  Universities and affiliated colleges in the restricted areas of the State which fall under the jurisdiction of the Commissioner, Municipal Corporation / Municipality or District Collector and Chairman, District Disaster Management Authority, in consultation with the respective University,  With this in mind, the concerned universities and colleges should take necessary steps to start regular classes by starting universities and colleges.  In this case, the concerned universities should issue instructions to start colleges with the consent of the local authorities.  2.  Govt. Circular No. Narrow 2021 / Pr.No.6 / Vishi-33  As per the guidelines of the University Grants Commission dated November 5, 2020, up to 50% of the students should be admitted to the class on rotation basis considering the availability of space.  8.  Central and State Government guidelines should be followed regarding Covid-19.  Also, the guidelines of the University Grants Commission dated November 5, 2020 should be strictly followed.  Also, the minutes of the meeting held on February 1, 2021 are being attached along with the necessary proceedings.  All concerned universities should take necessary action accordingly.  This Government Circular has been made available on the website of the Government of Maharashtra www.maharashtra.gov.in and its computer code is 202102031757424508

SE, TE, BE -  100% Syllabus (All 6 units)
FE -  70 % Syllabus (First 4 Units)
 
*Nature of SPPU Question Paper*
FE, SE, TE â€“ 50 Marks question paper having 50 Multiple choice questions (1 mark for each question)
 
BE - Question Paper will have A & B Sections. Total Marks= 70
Section A- 50 Multiple choice questions (1 mark for each question)
Section B- 20 Marks for Descriptive questions ( 4 questions- each question will have 5 marks)
All BE students have to type answers of these 4 questions on their mobile/laptop
 or
 Students have to write on a paper and scan it and upload it during exam

*Time for Exam:* 
FE, SE, TE â€“ 1 hours
BE - Approximately 1.5 to 2 Hrs (Yet not decided by SPPU)

*Date of Exams*
FE - 30 March 2021 onwards
SE, TE, BE - 15th March 2021 to 30th March 2021

16/03/21, 10:13 am - +91 70152 41319: Clarity, simplicity, and unity - provides both a framework for thinking about algorithms and a means of expressing those algorithms 

Orthogonality -every combination of features is meaningful

Naturalness for the application - program structure reflects the logical structure of algorithm

Support for abstraction - program data reflects problem being solved

Ease of program verification - verifying that program correctly performs its required function 

Programming environment - external support for the language

Portability of programs - transportability of the resulting programs from the computer on which they are developed to other computer systems

Cost of use - program execution, program translation, program creation, and program maintenance

Steps :

1. Google Account banao 
2. Apne Screenshot ke folder ko uss account ke saath sync kardo.
3. Apne dost ke paas wo login karwa do
4. apne phone mein bhi login karlo 

Exam shuru hone ke baad 

1. har ek question ka ss lelo 
        wo automatically tumahre photos mein chala jayega (toh tab/window change karne ki jarurat nahi)

3. Laptop ke bagal mein phone open rakho, starting ke 40 minute khud se jitne question ho wo karlo last ke 20 minute dost ne jitne comments add kiye wahaan se dkeh ke kardo (phone ko laptop ke side rkahna h )

2.Download at least three browsers like Mozilla, chrome etc.

4.download Microsoft Teams App and Free version Moodle App on your browser as a safer sideon Mobile
5.In Moodle free App give the link as https://moodle.aitpune.edu.in (Read more about Free Moodle app on google by typing free Moodle App)
6Connect to Microsoft teams Link sent by staff before 15 Min. start of the exam. Exam will start after everybody has joined the teams

17/05/21, 2:36 pm - Vaishnav: Highlighted text dekho....



Sir,
SPPU has introduced Honours/Minors  degree for Comp, IT, E&TC & Mech students from AY 2020-21 in following areas 
i) AI & ML 

ii) Cybersecurity 

iii) IoT 

iv) Augmented & Virtual Reality 

v) Data Science 

vi) Robotics 

vii) Blockchain Technology 



The detailed structure and syllabus of Honours/Minors  in various areas is in attachment. Details of (i) to (v) are forwarded in attachment. Details of (vi) & (vii) are not yet available.
Total teaching load per semester is 40 Hrs Theory and 20 Hrs Practical. *Assuming Rs. 2000/- Per Hour remuneration for the visiting/adjunct  faculty, total expenditure will be Rs. 1.20 Lakh. Additional Rs. 30,000/ per semester will be required for running these courses.  Total expenditure towards this will be Rs. 1.50 Lakh.*
Additional Fees can be charged as below depending on batch size to meet above expenditure. 
Batch Size 

Fees Per Semester (Rs.) 

60 

2500/-

40 

4000/-

20 

7500/-

A qualified faculty/expert who can conduct lectures and practical needs to be identified  for each of these programs. 
Dedicated faculty for each Honours/Minors course needs to be appointed to monitor the progress and conduct these programs  
The students can be given option to utilize balance amount of their Value Added Course(VAC) fees to pay part of this fees. 
Put up for your perusal and approval please.

06/06/21, 9:07 pm - +91 89996 19378: section .data
	msg1 db 10,13,"Enter a string:"
	len1 equ $-msg1

section .bss
	str1 resb 200                 ;string declaration
	result resb 16

section .text

global _start
	_start:

;display
	mov Rax,1
	mov Rdi,1
	mov Rsi,msg1
	mov Rdx,len1
	syscall

;store string 

	mov rax,0
	mov rdi,0
	mov rsi,str1
	mov rdx,200
	syscall

call display

;exit system call
	mov Rax ,60
	mov Rdi,0
	syscall


%macro dispmsg 2
	mov Rax,1
	mov Rdi,1
	mov rsi,%1
	mov rdx,%2
	syscall
%endmacro



display:
	mov rbx,rax                      ; store no in rbx
	mov rdi,result                   ;point rdi to result variable 
	mov cx,16                        ;load count of rotation in cl  

	up1: 
		rol rbx,04               ;rotate no of left by four bits
		mov al,bl	         ; move lower byte in dl		
		and al,0fh               ;get only LSB
		cmp al,09h               ;compare with 39h
		jg add_37                ;if greater than 39h skip add 37    
		add al,30h                
		jmp skip                 ;else add 30     
	add_37: 
		add al,37h                 
	skip: 
		mov [rdi],al             ;store ascii code in result variable
		inc rdi                  ; point to next byte
		dec cx                   ; decrement counter
		jnz up1                  ; if not zero jump to repeat
		dispmsg result,16        ;call to macro
ret

CREATE TABLE customers(
    Customer_Id int ,
    First_Name varchar(25) ,
    Last_Name varchar(25) ,
    Birth_Date varchar(25) ,
    Join_Date date ,
    City varchar(45) ,
    State varchar(25) ,
    Street varchar(40) ,
    main_phone_num varchar(12) ,
    secondary_phone_num varchar(12) ,
    fax varchar(12) ,
    monthly_discount decimal(4, 2) ,
    pack_id int );
    
CREATE TABLE packages(
    pack_id int,
    speed varchar(10) ,
    strt_date date ,
    monthly_payment int ,
    sector_id int );
CREATE TABLE sectors(
    sector_id int ,
    sector_name varchar(10) );
CREATE TABLE pack_grades(
    grade_id int,
    grade_name varchar(25),
    min_price int,
    max_price int);

CREATE TABLE customers(
    Customer_Id int,
    First_Name varchar(25) ,
    Last_Name varchar(25) ,
    Birth_Date varchar(25) ,
    Join_Date date ,
    City varchar(45) ,
    State varchar(25) ,
    Street varchar(40) ,
    main_phone_num varchar(12) ,
    secondary_phone_num varchar(12) ,
    fax varchar(12) ,
    monthly_discount decimal(4, 2) ,
    pack_id int

);
    
CREATE TABLE packages(
    pack_id int,
    speed varchar(10) ,
    strt_date date ,
    monthly_payment int ,
    sector_id int
    );
    
CREATE TABLE sectors(
    sector_id int primary key,
    sector_name varchar(10) );
    
CREATE TABLE pack_grades(
    grade_id int,
    grade_name varchar(25),
    min_price int,
    max_price int);

/*
Customers and internet packages (Customersâ€¯&â€¯Packagesâ€¯tables) â€“ 

Write a query to display first name, last name, package number and internet speed for all customers. 

Writeâ€¯a query to display first name, last name, package number and internet speed for all customers whose package number equals 22 or 27. Order the query in ascending order by last name. 

*/
select First_Name, Last_Name, customers.pack_id, packages.speed from customers inner join packages on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id;
select First_Name, Last_Name, customers.pack_id, packages.speed from customers inner join packages on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id where (customers.pack_id = 22 or  customers.pack_id = 27) order by Last_Name;


/*
Internet packages and sectors â€“ 

Display the package number, internet speed, monthly payment and sector name for all packages (Packagesâ€¯andâ€¯Sectorsâ€¯tables). 

Displayâ€¯theâ€¯customer name, package number, internet speed, monthly payment and sector name for all customersâ€¯(Customers,â€¯Packagesâ€¯andâ€¯Sectorsâ€¯tables). 

Displayâ€¯theâ€¯customer name, package number, internet speed, monthly payment and sector name for allâ€¯customers in the business sectorâ€¯(Customers,â€¯Packagesâ€¯andâ€¯Sectorsâ€¯tables). 
*/

select pack_id, speed, monthly_payment, packages.sector_id, sectors.sector_name from packages inner join sectors on sectors.sector_id = packages.sector_id;
select customers.First_Name, customers.pack_id, speed, monthly_payment, sectors.sector_name from packages inner join customers on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id inner join sectors on sectors.sector_id = packages.sector_id;
select customers.First_Name, customers.pack_id, speed, monthly_payment, sectors.sector_name from packages inner join customers on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id inner join sectors on sectors.sector_id = packages.sector_id where(sectors.sector_id = 2);

/*
Display the last name, first name, join date, package number, internet speed and sector name for all customers in the private sector whoâ€¯joined the company in the year 2006. 
*/

select Last_Name, First_Name, customers.Join_Date, customers.pack_id, speed, sectors.sector_name from packages inner join customers on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id inner join sectors on sectors.sector_id = packages.sector_id where (customers.Join_Date = 2006);



/*
Display the package number, internet speed, monthly payment and package grade for all packages  whose monthly payment is between min_price and max_price(Packagesâ€¯andâ€¯Pack_Gradesâ€¯tables). 
*/
select pack_id, speed, monthly_payment, pack_grades.grade_name from packages inner join pack_grades on (pack_grades.min_price < packages.monthly_payment and pack_grades.max_price > packages.monthly_payment);

/*

Customers and internet packages (Customersâ€¯andâ€¯Packagesâ€¯tables) 

Display the first name, last name, internet speed and monthly payment for all customers. Use INNER JOIN to solve this exercise. 

Modify last query toâ€¯display all customers, including those without any internet package. 

Modify last query toâ€¯display all packages, including those without any customers. 

Modify last query toâ€¯display all packages and all customers. 
*/

select First_Name, Last_Name, customers.pack_id, packages.speed, packages.monthly_payment from customers inner join packages on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id;
select First_Name, Last_Name, customers.pack_id, packages.speed, packages.monthly_payment from customers left join packages on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id;
select First_Name, Last_Name, customers.pack_id, packages.speed, packages.monthly_payment from customers right join packages on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id;

select First_Name, Last_Name, customers.pack_id, packages.speed, packages.monthly_payment from customers left join packages on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id
union
select First_Name, Last_Name, customers.pack_id, packages.speed, packages.monthly_payment from customers right join packages on customers.pack_id = packages.pack_id;



/*

 

Display the last name, first name and package number for all customers who have the same package number as customer named â€˜A Taylorâ€™ (Customersâ€¯table). 

Display the last name, first name and monthly discount for all customers whose monthly discount is lower than the monthly discount of employee number 103 (Customersâ€¯table). 

Display the package number and internet speed for all packages whose internet speed is equal to the internet speed of package number 10 (Packagesâ€¯table). 

 
*/

select A.First_Name, A.Last_Name , A.pack_id from customers A, customers B where( B.First_Name = "Harland" and A.pack_id = B.pack_id);
select A.pack_id, A.speed from packages A, packages B where(A.speed <= B.speed and B.pack_id = 10);

25/09/21, 10:24 am - +91 77963 88728: Hi
We meet today from 11 am to 1 pm.
I will cover
1) Toy example on interfaces, to explain the syntax.
2) Concept and Example on multithreading.
3) Suspending and Activating threads using interrupts 
4) Concept and need of Thread pooling in our project.
5) Make a thread pool (custom) to have 100 threads ready for dispatch as a client request comes and  return to the pool after process (recycling threads).

 *This meeting will not be recorded, in person attendence is mandatory.* 

Regards

Director sir told the students that AIT will give 10% compensation in fees to the students whose Attendance will be more 85%. Despite all such things, we respect you a lot.
